      },
      "date": "2015-09-16 02:45:09.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nThis looks like a good improvement, but it diverges the Lustre version of fsx further from the upstream version, which is most uptodate in xfstests these days.  It would be best to use the same O_DIRECT changes from:\n\nhttp://oss.sgi.com/cgi-bin/gitweb.cgi?p=xfs/cmds/xfstests.git;a=blob;f=ltp/fsx.c\n\nIn particular, commit http://oss.sgi.com/cgi-bin/gitweb.cgi?p=xfs/cmds/xfstests.git;a=commitdiff;h=cad234da750aceb563992d95a0b14379740aedc6 adds O_DIRECT support.  You should also reference the upstream source of this code in your commit message.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "1cf512f63d61ac0679e4dbb88c56f41252de805c",
